d a controlling interest in gm durant took back control of the company after one of the most dramatic proxy wars in american business history durant then reorganized general motors company into general motors corporation in  merging chevrolet with gm and merging general motors of canada limited as an ally in  shortly thereafter he again lost control this time for good after the new vehicle market collapsed alfred p sloan was picked to take charge of the corporation and led it to its postwar global dominance when the seven manufacturing facilities operated by chevrolet before gm acquired the company began to contribute to gm operations these facilities were added to the individual factories that were exclusive to cadillac buick oldsmobile oakland and other companies acquired by gm this unprecedented growth of gm would last into the early s when it employed  workers and operated  assembly plantscitation needed chapter  bankruptcyedit main article general motors chapter  reorganization on june   after heavy losses general motors went bankrupt stockholders lost essentially all of their investment the nd generation buick lacrosse has been cited as an example of a gms revival following its restructing in the aftermath of the great recession on july   general motors emerged from government backed chapter  reorganization after an initial filing on june   through the troubled asset relief program the us treasury invested  billion in general motors and recovered  billion when it sold its shares on december   resulting in a loss of  billion the treasury invested an additional  billion into gms former financing company gmac now ally the shares in ally were sold on december   for  billion netting  billion a study by the center for automotive research found that the gm bailout saved  million jobs and preserved  billion in tax revenue also in  as part general motors chapter  bankruptcy the company shed several brands closing saturn pontiac and hummer while selling saab automobile 