ies versatile light commercial vehicle tf series pickups and isuzu bus chassis formed in  gmeas facility is the largest assembler of commercial vehicles in the region exporting to east and central african countries including uganda tanzania malawi rwanda and burundi in addition to assembly gmea also markets the chevrolet products spark and optracitation needed in the s miller brothers nigeria was founded as an importer of commercial vehicles of the bedford brand into the country in  the company opened its own assembly plant and operated under the name nigernigeria motors in  the plant and its distribution network was split into different companies and renamed as federated motors industries in  the company was taken in by a joint venture between general motors and uacn of nigeriacitation needed oceaniaedit in australia gm has been represented by the holden brand since  gm having acquired the company in  in  gm opel cars began to be imported into australia as a niche marque under their own brand name however as of august  gm has made the decision to remove the opel brand from australia noting poor adoption and sales in new zealand gm was represented by chevrolet pontiac and vauxhall cars – all locally assembled since  fully imported holdens appeared in  new zealand assembly of holdens begun in  was slowly phased in through the early s to replace most vauxhall and all chevrolet cars thirty years later australia tariff protection was removed and local assembly plants closed in  and  gm became a national sales company and a parts distribution centrecitation needed in the early s general motors new zealand sold a few isuzu and opel models rebranded as holdens when new zealands gm was renamed holden in  on december   gm announced that holden would cease engine and vehicle manufacturing operations in australia by the end of  beyond  holdens australian presence will consist of a national sales company a parts distribution centre and a global design studio motorsportsedit thi