on september   in flint michigan as a holding company controlled by william c durant owner of buick at the beginning of the th century there were fewer than  automobiles in america and durant had become a leading manufacturer of horsedrawn vehicles in flint before making his foray into the automotive industry gms cofounder was charles stewart mott whose carriage company was merged into buick prior to gms creation over the years mott became the largest single stockholder in gm and spent his life with his mott foundation which has benefited the city of flint his adopted home gm acquired oldsmobile later that year in  durant brought in cadillac elmore oakland and several others also in  gm acquired the reliance motor truck company of owosso michigan and the rapid motor vehicle company of pontiac michigan the predecessors of gmc truck durant along with r s mclaughlin lost control of gm in  to a bankers trust because of the large amount of debt taken on in its acquisitions coupled with a collapse in new vehicle sales the longestlived continuous automobile nameplate still in production in the world is the chevrolet suburban the next year durant started the chevrolet motor car company in the us and in canada in  and through this he secretly purchased a controlling interest in gm durant took back control of the company after one of the most dramatic proxy wars in american business history durant then reorganized general motors company into general motors corporation in  merging chevrolet with gm and merging general motors of canada limited as an ally in  shortly thereafter he again lost control this time for good after the new vehicle market collapsed alfred p sloan was picked to take charge of the corporation and led it to its postwar global dominance when the seven manufacturing facilities operated by chevrolet before gm acquired the company began to contribute to gm operations these facilities were added to the individual factories that were exclusive to cadillac buick oldsmobile oakland and other companies acquired by gm this unprecedented growth of gm would last into the early s when it employed  workers and operated  assembly plantscitation needed chapter  bankruptcyedit main article general motors chapter  reorganization on june   after heavy losses general motors went bankrupt stockholders lost essentially all of their investment the nd generation buick lacrosse has been cited as an example of a gms revival following its restructing in the aftermath of the great recession on july   general motors emerged from government backed chapter  reorganization after an initial filing on june   through the troubled asset relief program the us treasury invested  billion in general motors and recovered  billion when it sold its shares on december   resulting in a loss of  billion the treasury invested an additional  billion into gms former financing company gmac now ally the shares in ally were sold on december   for  billion netting  billion a study by the center for automotive research found that the gm bailout saved  million jobs and preserved  billion in tax revenue also in  as part general motors chapter  bankruptcy the company shed several brands closing saturn pontiac and hummer while selling saab automobile to dutch automaker spyker and emerged from a governmentbacked chapter  reorganization in  the reorganized gm made an initial public offering that was one of the worlds top five largest ipos to date and returned to profitability later that year corporate governanceedit gm world headquarters in detroit based on global sales general motors is routinely among the worlds largest automakers headquartered at the renaissance center in detroit gm employs approximately  people around the world in  general motors sold  million cars and trucks globally in  it sold  million as of march update mary barra is the chief executive officer ceo and chairman of the board and daniel ammann is the president the head of design edward t welburn was the first african american to lead a global automotive design organization and as of update the highest ranking african american in the us motor industry as part of the companys advertising ed whitacre announced the companys day moneyback guarantee and repayment of  billion loan from government ahead of schedule on december   gm announced that mary barra  executive vice president global product development purchasing and supply chain was elected by the board of directors to become the next ceo of the company succeeding dan akerson on january   barra also joined the gm board from june  to march  the company had three chief executive officers and three chief financial officers financial resultsedit the company has reported annual profits since  it can carry forward previous losses to reduce tax liability on future earnings it earned  billion in  the wall street journal estimated the tax break including credits for costs related to pensions and other expenses can be worth as much as  billion over the next  years in  general motors ranked second on the list with  million units produced globally in  gm returned to the first place with  million units sold worldwide corresponding to  market share of the global motor vehicle industry the top two markets in  were china with  units and the united states with  vehicles sold the chevrolet brand was the main contributor to gm performance with  million vehicles sold around the world in  a global sales record in may  during a commencement speech ceo dan akerson suggested that gm was on the cusp of rejoining the sp  index gm was removed from the index as it approached bankruptcy in  on april   cnnmoney reported that gm profits fell to  million for the first three months of  gm now estimates the cost of their  recall due to faulty ignition switches which have been linked to at least  deaths at  billion shares of gm were down  for the year before the new announcement of gms lower profits on january   fortune reported that gm led a bn equ